 {"id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.2","title":"Mark Command: cass-memory mark (Feedback Recording)","description":"# Feature: Mark Command

## Purpose
Record bullet usage feedback. This is how the playbook learns:
- Mark helpful when a rule helps you succeed
- Mark harmful when following a rule causes problems

## Usage
```bash
cass-memory mark b-abc123 --helpful
cass-memory mark b-abc123 --harmful --reason "Caused test failures"
cass-memory mark b-abc123 --helpful --session ~/.claude/sessions/abc.jsonl
```

## Implementation
```typescript
async function markCommand(
  bulletId: string,
  flags: { helpful?: boolean; harmful?: boolean; reason?: string; session?: string }
): Promise<void> {
  const config = await loadConfig();
  const playbook = await loadMergedPlaybook(config);

  // Find bullet
  const bullet = findBullet(playbook, bulletId);
  if (!bullet) {
    error(`Bullet not found: ${bulletId}`);
    process.exit(1);
  }

  // Create feedback event WITH TIMESTAMP (P1 - critical for decay)
  const event: FeedbackEvent = {
    type: flags.helpful ? "helpful" : "harmful",
    timestamp: now(),
    sessionPath: flags.session,
    reason: flags.reason
  };

  // Add event to bullet
  bullet.feedbackEvents.push(event);

  // Update legacy counts (for backwards compatibility)
  if (flags.helpful) bullet.helpfulCount++;
  else bullet.harmfulCount++;

  // Update timestamps
  bullet.updatedAt = now();

  // Recalculate state
  bullet.state = calculateMaturityState(bullet, config);

  // Save playbook
  await savePlaybook(playbook, config.playbookPath);

  // Also log to usage.jsonl for audit trail
  await appendUsageLog({
    bulletId,
    event,
    effectiveScoreAfter: getEffectiveScore(bullet, config)
  });

  output({
    success: true,
    bulletId,
    event,
    newState: bullet.state,
    effectiveScore: getEffectiveScore(bullet, config)
  }, formatMarkResult, flags);
}
```

## Usage Log Format
```
~/.cass-memory/usage.jsonl
{"bulletId":"b-abc123","type":"helpful","timestamp":"2025-12-07T10:30:00Z","session":"..."}
{"bulletId":"b-def456","type":"harmful","timestamp":"2025-12-07T11:00:00Z","reason":"..."}
```

## State Transitions After Mark
- If new harmful feedback pushes ratio > 30%: state → "retired"
- If helpful feedback reaches 10 with ratio < 10%: state → "proven"
- Automatic decay recalculation happens on every read

## Output
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "bulletId": "b-abc123",
  "event": {
    "type": "helpful",
    "timestamp": "2025-12-07T10:30:00Z"
  },
  "newState": "proven",
  "effectiveScore": 15.2
}
