 {"id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.7","title":"Forget Command + Toxic Bullet Log (P8)","description":"# Feature: Forget Command + Toxic Bullet Log (P8)

## Purpose
Permanently block a pattern that should NEVER be suggested again.
More severe than deprecation - this is for truly harmful patterns
that caused production issues, security problems, etc.

## Usage
```bash
cass-memory forget b-abc123 --reason "Caused production outage"
cass-memory forget --list  # Show toxic bullet log
```

## Difference from Deprecation
| Aspect | Deprecate | Forget |
|--------|-----------|--------|
| Reversible | Yes | No (requires manual edit) |
| Stays in playbook | Yes (marked deprecated) | Removed entirely |
| Future proposals | Allowed | Blocked via semantic matching |
| Audit trail | In playbook | In toxic_bullets.log |

## Implementation
```typescript
async function forgetCommand(
  bulletId: string,
  flags: { reason: string; list?: boolean }
): Promise<void> {
  if (flags.list) {
    return listToxicBullets();
  }

  const config = await loadConfig();
  const playbook = await loadMergedPlaybook(config);

  // Find bullet
  const bullet = findBullet(playbook, bulletId);
  if (!bullet) {
    error(`Bullet not found: ${bulletId}`);
    process.exit(1);
  }

  // Log to toxic bullets file BEFORE removing
  await appendToxicLog({
    id: bullet.id,
    content: bullet.content,
    reason: flags.reason,
    forgottenAt: now(),
    originalBullet: bullet
  });

  // Remove from playbook
  playbook.bullets = playbook.bullets.filter(b => b.id !== bulletId);

  await savePlaybook(playbook, config.playbookPath);

  output({
    success: true,
    bulletId,
    action: "forgotten",
    reason: flags.reason
  }, formatForgetResult, flags);
}
```

## Toxic Bullet Log Format
```
~/.cass-memory/toxic_bullets.log
# One JSON object per line
{"id":"b-abc123","content":"Use eval() for dynamic code execution","reason":"Security vulnerability - allows code injection","forgottenAt":"2025-12-07T10:30:00Z"}
```

## Blocking Future Proposals
When the curator processes new "add" deltas, check against toxic log:
```typescript
async function isSemanticallyToxic(
  content: string,
  toxicPatterns: ToxicEntry[]
): Promise<boolean> {
  for (const toxic of toxicPatterns) {
    const similarity = jaccardSimilarity(content, toxic.content);
    if (similarity > 0.7) {
      log(`Blocked: "${content}" matches toxic pattern "${toxic.content}"`);
      return true;
    }
  }
  return false;
}
```

## Cascading Toxic Logs
Both global and repo-level toxic logs are checked:
```typescript
const globalToxic = await loadToxicLog("~/.cass-memory/toxic_bullets.log");
const repoToxic = await loadToxicLog("./.cass/toxic.log");
const allToxic = [...globalToxic, ...repoToxic];
```

