 {"id":"cass_memory_system-0ew.8","title":"Doctor Command: System Health Check (P13)","description":"# Feature: Doctor Command (P13 - 5× DX Impact)

## Purpose
Comprehensive system health check. Catches configuration issues, missing
dependencies, stale data, and other problems BEFORE they cause failures.

## Usage
```bash
cass-memory doctor
cass-memory doctor --fix  # Auto-fix simple issues
cass-memory doctor --json
```

## Checks Performed

### 1. Configuration Checks
- Config file exists and is valid JSON
- Required fields present
- API key environment variables set
- Paths are writable

### 2. Dependency Checks  
- cass is available and healthy
- cass index is up to date
- LLM API is reachable (optional ping)

### 3. Data Integrity Checks
- Playbook YAML is valid
- No orphaned bullet references
- No circular deprecation chains
- feedbackEvents timestamps are valid ISO 8601

### 4. Health Metrics
- Bullets with negative effective scores
- Stale bullets (no feedback in 90+ days)
- High harmful ratio bullets
- Duplicate content detection

## Implementation
```typescript
interface DoctorCheck {
  name: string;
  status: "pass" | "warn" | "fail";
  message: string;
  fixable?: boolean;
  fix?: () => Promise<void>;
}

async function doctorCommand(flags: { fix?: boolean; json?: boolean }): Promise<void> {
  const checks: DoctorCheck[] = [];

  // Configuration checks
  checks.push(await checkConfigExists());
  checks.push(await checkConfigValid());
  checks.push(await checkApiKeys());

  // Dependency checks
  checks.push(await checkCassAvailable());
  checks.push(await checkCassIndex());

  // Data integrity checks
  checks.push(await checkPlaybookValid());
  checks.push(await checkNoOrphanedRefs());
  checks.push(await checkNoCircularDeprecations());
  checks.push(await checkTimestampsValid());

  // Health metrics
  checks.push(await checkNegativeScoreBullets());
  checks.push(await checkStaleBullets());
  checks.push(await checkHighHarmfulRatio());
  checks.push(await checkDuplicateContent());

  // Auto-fix if requested
  if (flags.fix) {
    for (const check of checks.filter(c => c.status !== "pass" && c.fixable)) {
      await check.fix?.();
      check.status = "pass";
      check.message += " (auto-fixed)";
    }
  }

  // Output
  output({ checks, summary: summarizeChecks(checks) }, formatDoctorResult, flags);

  // Exit code based on results
  const hasFailures = checks.some(c => c.status === "fail");
  if (hasFailures) process.exit(1);
}
```

